description:
Job responsibilities:
- A variety of Quality checks; Testing and Release of products within the Inspection framework by the Products received.  Product shipments, and Products returned from customers;
- Use of a company issued inspection control stamp to release or quarantine products;
- Requests all missing or incorrect documents from Suppliers and Manufacturers for products received and pursue the problem until resolution has been achieved;
- Scanning and keywork filing of Certificates, Drawings, etc. in Docuware;
- Loading delivery documents in the system and archiving.  Management and custodial oversight of the Documentation Archive;
- Manage Quality documentation and support other generic office/warehouse duties.

Job requirements:
- Technical trade school and/or Commercial experience in the metal sector and/or experience in Quality control, able to distinguish between standard and special constructive products.
- The Position candidate will keep up-to-date technical knowledge and education requirements.


Language & skills:
- Language: Cantonese, English, Mandarin
- Computer: MS Office

Responsibilities:

Able to utilize available resources to achieve the maximum output within the available maintenance slot period;
Coordinate Maintenance activity planning actions in support of production plans with other concerned activities;
Schedule and conduct all Maintenance scheduling meetings;
Manage and control various man hour booking, cost, material, trend analysis, etc.;
Distribute Daily, Weekly and Monthly production KPI reports to authorized users;
Review training schedule to minimize impact on production;
Ensure appropriate communication throughout the delivery of the Maintenance Activities;
Carry out any other duties that are assigned by Operations Manager

Requirements:

At least 5 years experience in Aviation MRO environment. Familiarity with resource and material planning;
Excellent communication skills and ability to communicate info and data to all levels in the organization;
Ability to think analytically and solve problems efficiently and effectively;
Ability to work under intense pressure in MRO environment;
Extensive knowledge of monitoring work schedules and creating backup plans;
Knowledge of PC and Microsoft office applications. MS Project skill is essential;
Ability to communicate in English both orally and in writing
